:)</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/uwraithwavefeaamael.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Wraithwave FeaAmael</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Apprentice</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(1/5/01 5:56:10 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm10.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=28.topic&index=10>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Wizard Familiar...</span><hr size=1> To add to everyone else, yes, this is a wonderfully creative idea.  I partially agree with the previous post about being totally opposed to pets of any kind.  However, the thought of a familiar with mana regen, or HP buff, AC buff, INT buff, is very inviting.  My main point is this...  and most other casters will disagree...    If you read fantasy style stories, the TRUE nature of a wizard actually encompasses ALL of the abilities of the other casters.  Wizards are masters of ALL mind and matter.  Therefore, a true wizard would be able to wake the dead(necromancers), change form and control minds(Enchanters), summon items or create monsters(magicians).<br>
<br>
So, since this ideology would never be used within Everquest, let me concentrate on the familiar and say that it would at LEAST scratch the surface of improving our overall usefulness.  I am not sure if it would make a huge dent... but boy would it look GREAT!!!!!<br>
