Wraithwave FeaA'mael<br>
53 Generation Channeler of Oira Feanor(The Eternal Spirit of Fire)<br>
Cazic-Thule <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/unitewavemojomaster.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Nitewave Mojomaster</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Apprentice</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(1/5/01 6:10:41 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm10.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=28.topic&index=11>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> familiar behavior</span><hr size=1> Sure, I like the idea of a familiar.  It's an interesting idea.  However, how would it behave?  Rather than making Verant come up with some behavior perhaps we as a community can figure out the best way for our familiar to act.<br>
<br>
Do we want several different types of familiars?  Maybe one that sings a *personal* clarity song, one that increases resistances, and one that acts as a focus item.  By distributing some of the tasks wizards really want among several familiars, they force us to choose the right one for the right situation and still make compromises.<br>
<br>
What about dungeon crawling?  Personally, I would like the ability to park my familiar if its pathing was becoming a problem.  Given that, though, there are tons of places where you would not want to pull one because of the pathing.  Other pet casting classes are limited in this respect as well, so I would not feel cheated.<br>
<br>
Does the familiar have any offensive capability?  It would probably be best if it didn't, but there's one idea I like:  having a low hitpoint familiar that only attacked when the wizard got hit by melee.  The point is to keep wizards conscious about how much aggro they cause and to not make the familiar so powerful it wouldn't just be smacked in a round or two by some mob.<br>
<br>
What kind of downside would a familiar have?  There's the old &quot;wizard takes damage if someone kills it&quot; idea.  But killing something that doesn't have offensive capability?  That would just be a matter of staying out of AE range.  Maybe the familiar is a buff icon you can switch off, but also reduces the total number of buffs you can get because you've put one on yourself.<br>
<br>
Given all of that, I think Verant's reply would be along the lines of &quot;a bard does all of that, just group with them&quot; and &quot;we don't want to reduce the amount of class interdependence&quot;.<br>
<br>
The only thing that a familiar might do that a bard couldn't would be to act as a focus item that either reduced mana cost or increased the caster's ability (damage, resistance check, etc.).  They've already done this with the specializations.  Our DDs already cost less to cast because of that.<br>
<br>
A familiar is a wonderful idea but I don't think Verant will go for it.  (I'm playing devil's advocate here...give me a familiar and I'll be the happiest little wizard you ever did see.)<br>
<br>
<br>
Nitewave Mojomaster<br>
Level 54 Dark Elf Wizard<br>
