Zeth<br>
Evoker<br>
Bristlebane <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/uvalgavgaav.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Valgav Gaav</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Apprentice</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(1/5/01 8:06:23 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm10.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=28.topic&index=13>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: !</span><hr size=1> My self i think its a great idea too. Although, i dont believe they should have several types of familiars. A familiar is a random thing, in fact D&amp;D its possible not to even find one. Would be nice to have a random of 2-4 different random familiars. Each with one specialized effect,and nothing else. Other then the look of some creature that is. <p>I contain the powers of the Ancient Dragons, and from my lord Gaav, the Deomon Dragon King!!! Do not underestimate me....
</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/ugibwigglestump.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Gib Wigglestump</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Apprentice</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(1/5/01 8:25:39 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm10.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=28.topic&index=14>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Wizards with a Familar?</span><hr size=1> <br>
Ok lets step back a sec.. while I love the idea.. look at it from outsiders point of veiw.<br>
<br>
1.  Wizards are masters of Evocation<br>
2.  Magicians are masters of summoning<br>
<br>
<br>
Now you have stated we would summon or conjure this familar to be with us.. which class does that fall under eh?<br>
<br>
Mages will bitch to HIGH hell<br>
<br>
Gib Wigglestump <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/usymbuloom.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Symbul Oom</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Apprentice</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(1/5/01 8:55:12 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm10.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=28.topic&index=15>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Wizard Familiar</span><hr size=1> I think having a little pet that follows us around and providing a small bit of ac/resist protection is something doable and palatable to the other classes.  Adding mana/hp regen is highly unlikely given that would unbalance our powers considerably (We have manaskin at 52 already, doesn't do much but every little bit helps).  Having a familiar should be more focused on adding extra &quot;flavor&quot; to our characters.  For example, a wizzie could have only one particular type of familiar and this would involve a quest for each type (much like choosing a spell specialization).  That way we don't fall into the other classes ability to call up different pets to suit the situation, and it fits more into the wizzy roleplaying style of having one permanent familiar.  Making the familiar give only small stat/buff/resist enhancement also gets away from everyone choosing the same pet (everyone would be running around with the mana/hp regen one if that was an option) and giving us the ability to give the pet a name would also further seperate us from mages/necros (do you really want a familiar named jabortik/Gobnerb/etc?)  There are already several mob models suitable for familiars (bixie, pixie, wisp) so this wouldn't be too hard to implement. It would also be fun to allow some limited social control over the pets too.<br>
<br>
Symbul Oom<br>
52 Wizzy on Torv <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=faerwynd>Faerwynd</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Apprentice</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(1/5/01 9:07:08 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm10.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=28.topic&index=16>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Balance</span><hr size=1> I have to put my 2cp in- I think it's a great idea first off.  However, when we/Graffe approach Verant with this I think we should have our ducks in a row.  Yes, magicians are going to raise holy hell.  The only way I personally think we could minimize this is to all agree that it is a nocombatant, and has some repercussions to dying.  I also like the idea of getting a random familiar out of some short list, with different effects on all of them.  We could also have this implemented as a quest- Tunare knows we wizzies need some more- however, preferably a quest that doesn't involve us killing a MOB that spawns 13 times a RL year.  As far as the graphic list goes- we could have Verant implement this with one standard graphic- w/possibly a variable color denoting which familiar it is.  Just a thought, but I can't see that Verant can give us an unqualified 'NO' if we approach this in a thoughtfull manner.<br>
<br>
Faerwynd Corpserunner<br>
 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/uaureltcerosst.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Aurelt CeRosst</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Apprentice</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(1/5/01 9:17:18 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm10.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=28.topic&index=17>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Wizards with a Familar?</span><hr size=1> I agree with Wraithweave....we are the only pure casters who don't get a companion...even druids and shamen get pets and they're not typically considered 'pure' casters. I have shelf upon shelf of fantasy novels and myth and lore from history. Wizards have Familiars... <br>
<br>
I play Dungeons and Dragons (all 3 editions) and that's something that is generally agreed on, wizards are the casters that run the gauntlet of abilities...they can cast from every school of magic, they're just not SUPER good at any one. Kinda like Druids are in EQ...they can do everything...just not any one thing extreemly well. Every other caster can nuke to a certain extent...what can we summon? an eye of zomm? what can we charm...nothing that I know of....what can we change ourselves into...nothing that I know of...we only have 2 buffs I can think of that we can give someone else (besides levitate and invis)...I don't see where letting us have a familiar will unbalance us with the other classes. none of the things a familiar can give us is as good as what the other classes can contribute and since we've been self only buffs for so long I think the benifits from a familiar should stay for us only. I don't think they should affect the whole group. I also rather like the idea that if your familiar dies you take damage...but something else that they've implimented in 3rd edition D&amp;D tha I like is that you lose exp if your familiar dies. Would make Wizards very consious of where their familiar is and what's happening to them. The only other point I have is that the familiar should not be KOS or get agroed unless it attacks first or the wizard is under agro.<br>
<br>
--<br>
Aurelt CeRosst<br>
Wizard of the 29th Casting; officer Valkyrians of Norrath <br>
Xegony <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/uonari.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Onari</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Apprentice</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(1/5/01 9:43:29 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm10.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=28.topic&index=18>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Familiars</span><hr size=1> I think the idea of familiars is fabulous.  Pets would be too powerful, so a non-combatant familiar would be perfect.  I think that they should be summon spells (mages can nuke, why can't we summon??)  and they should get more powerful and have better buffs as you go up in level.  If the familiar dies, you should take an amount of damage equal to the familiars HP, and get stunned for x amount of time (to deal with the severed link between you and it)  It should be like a buff, and stay with you when zoning.  You should also be able to store it (like in a backpack, BG2 anyone?)  so that if you don't want to watch it, you don't have to.  Just make it so that if it's stowed away, the buffs it gives you are not active.  Also, don't make it give ultra buffs, just little things like +2 int, or mana regen of half a breeze.  Definitely no group stuff, we are all about personal buffs (flicker flames are a VI joke).<br>
<br>
Just my 2 cp<br>
Onari Spellweaver<br>
30th Wizard, Clan Blackwatch<br>
Cazic-Thule Server <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/ujaynara.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Jaynara</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/white_purplespot.gif BORDER=0 WIDTH=10 HEIGHT=10></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Apprentice</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(1/5/01 9:47:51 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm10.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=28.topic&index=19>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Wizard Familiar</span><hr size=1> I love this idea.  I have enjoyed playing a wizard immensely. My only issue is that at some times I feel very dependent on Ench/Bard for the mana regen.   I think that I am pretty good at Mana management, but in some fast paced battles I cant keep up. A lil pet that would be strictly an enhancement would be great. A mana regen, perhaps a dmg shield or a HP buff.  Maybe make it so the preferred ones, i.e. mana regen, cost more mana and have more of an adverse effect when they die. <br>
<br>
Jaynara Spiritwalker<br>
53rd Channeler<br>
Undivided Faith<br>
Drinal Shard <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/ubalrigard.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Balrigard</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Wizard</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(1/5/01 10:04:31 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm10.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=28.topic&index=20>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Wizards with a Familar?</span><hr size=1> I love the idea, but VI will never go with it, but what the heck lets roll with it.<br>
<br>
I like the idea of a minor AC/HP/MANA buff. But lets look more into the RolePlaying aspect of this. Instead of the same Familiar for all. How about 1 familiar per Diety. You worship Cazic you get a Golem or something. Agnostic's I think would be screwed. (darn I'm agnostic) Or 1 per Race/Diety would even be better. Help define the background of who you really are in EQ. <br>
<br>
Just a thought.<br>
<br>
Balrigard<br>
